3. Term. The term of this Public License is specified in Section 6(a).

4. Media and formats; technical modifications allowed. The Licensor authorizes You to exercise the Licensed Rights in all media and formats whether now known or hereafter created, and to make technical modifications necessary to do so. The Licensor waives and/or agrees not to assert any right or claim in the Licensed Material under Section 2(a)(4) to the limited extent necessary to allow You to exercise the Licensed Rights in all media and formats.

5. Downstream recipients. The Licensor's grant to You includes the right to grant the rights conveyed under this Public License to third parties.

b. Other rights.

1. Moral rights, such as the right of integrity, are not licensed under this Public License to the extent they exist.

2. Patent and trademark rights are not licensed under this Public License.

3. To the extent possible, the Licensor waives any right to collect royalties from You for the exercise of the Licensed Rights, whether directly or through a collecting society.

c. Limitations and exceptions. No trademark or patent rights are licensed under this Public License.

